Component Fiber
|
|— memoizedState (first hook)
     |
     |— hook1 (state A)
     |     memoizedState: valueA
     |
     |— hook2 (state B)
           memoizedState: valueB

           React keeps a linked list of hooks for each component inside its Fiber tree.

Each useState creates a hook object:

hook = {
  memoizedState: current value,
  queue: pending updates,
  next: pointer to next hook
}


During each render:

React walks through this hook list

Provides the correct state in correct order

Applies queued updates from setState